French President Emmanuel Macron, Italian Prime Minister Mario Draghi and German Chancellor Olaf Scholz met with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy in Kyiv after visiting the town of Irpin on Thursday, Ukraine 24 reported. "It's an important moment. It's a message of unity we're sending to the Ukrainians," French President Emmanuel Macron said after pulling into Kyiv on an overnight train along with Germany's Olaf Scholz and Italy's Mario Draghi. They were also joined by Romanian President Klaus Iohannis. (With input from Reuters) (Cover: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy greets French President Emmanuel Macron as German Chancellor Olaf Scholz and Italian Prime Minister Mario Draghi stand outside the Mariyinsky Palace, in Kyiv, Ukraine June 16, 2022. /Reuters)